.RH MOD.RECIPES-SOURCE APPLESAUCE-SLD SL "24 Nov 87" 1988
.RZ "APPLESAUCE SALAD" "Applesauce jello salad"
A delicious jello salad, taken from "The Monterey Coast
Guard Officers' Wives Club Cookbook."  My sister-in-law
was the president of the club which put that cookbook
together.
.IH "Serves 8"
.IG "\(14 cup" "cinnamon imperials" "100 g"
(candy)
.IG "1 cup" "water" "250 ml"
.IG "3 oz" "lemon jello mix" "100 g"
(1 small package)
.IG "1 cup" "applesauce" "250 ml"
.IG "4\-5" "ice cubes"
.PH
.SK 1
Place the candy and water in a pot.  Bring to a boil,
stirring to dissolve the candy.  
.SK 2
Add jello powder and stir until it is dissolved.
.SK 3
Stir in applesauce and ice cubes until ice cubes
are melted.
.SK 4
Pour into a bowl and refrigerate until set (1 hour or more).
.NX
Substituting apple cider or apple juice for the water adds
tremendous taste.  We prefer homemade "chunky"
style applesauce to processed commercial brands.
.SH RATING
.I Difficulty:
easy.
.I Time:
10 minutes preparation, 1\-3 hours to chill.
.I Precision:
approximate measurement OK.
.WR
